|valign="top"|[[File:Sigüenza - Sepulcro de Martín Vázquez de Arce.jpg|thumb|100px|The 15th-century arcosolium of Martín Vázquez de Arce, in the wall of the Cathedral of [[Sigüenza|Sigüenza, Spain]]. Like most post-Roman era arcosolia, this tomb is above ground. The alabaster figure on the lid of the sarcophagus is the famous ''el doncel de Sigüenza'', "the boy of Sigüenza".]]
